stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: Phishing Email with UPS Theme
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description: Between 26 and 27 January 2016, a Government Department was targeted with a phishing email with the subject "UPS Delivery Notification: Not delivered. Tracking Number 0W9026256087832073149" with an attached .zip file from totaltrack@ups.com. The file 4036125.bat (MD5 3880EEB1C736D853EB13B44898B718AB) attempts to call out to the following domains hecalrighco.ru, pakepema.ru ,novetajec.ru, and daissaval.es through port 80.

stix:Indicator.indicator:Title: Malicious E-mail Indicator
stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
------BEGIN EMAIL HEADER------ Subject: UPS Delivery Notification: Not delivered. Tracking Number 0W9026256087832073149 From: UPS Delivery Notification <totaltrack@ups.com>; SMTP From: php-sender-tss-plitka.ru@undeliverable.masterhost.ru; To: [REDACTED]; Date: Wed Jan 27 16:31:29 GMT 2016 Received: from dbe611.hs.shared.masterhost.ru ([90.156.197.42])by relay1.shared.masterhost.ru with esmtpenvelope from <php-sender-tss-plitka.ru@undeliverable.masterhost.ru>message id 1aOT0D-0000qN-Qrfor [REDACTED]; Wed, 27 Jan 2016 19:31:30 +0300 Received: from u171423 by dbe611.hs.shared.masterhost.ru with local (Exim 4.80)(envelope-from <php-sender-tss-plitka.ru@undeliverable.masterhost.ru>)id 1aOT0D-0000Nn-Ow; Wed, 27 Jan 2016 19:31:29 +0300 X-PHP-Script: tss-plitka.ru/system/logs/zQT6LOW5Y95a2.php for 111.253.37.43, 111.253.37.43, 111.253.37.43 X-Mailer: PHP/5.4.1 Reply-To: pkginfo@ups.com Mime-Version: 1.0 Content-Type: multipart/mixed; boundary="----------mgjvhd" Message-Id: <E1aOT0D-0000Nn-Ow@dbe611.hs.shared.masterhost.ru> ------ END EMAIL HEADER ------
The "From" address associated with the email was spoofed to appear to be from a legitimate automated package tracking service.

stix:Indicator.indicator:Title: Malicious File Indicator
stix:Indicator.indicator:Description:
This malicious executable file was created and executed by a Microsoft Word macro started by the email attachment "4033968.exe" (specific file details were not provided for the attachment).
Upon execution, HTTP POST requests are sent to the following domains: hecalrighco.ru, pakepema.ru, and novetajec.ru, followed by a HTTP GET request to daissaval.es to retrieve a remote executable that would drop and execute in the User Local Temp directory.

stix:Indicator.indicator:Description: This file is the clean up script after litigation.exe (MD5 D9EA282A972988717AF617799678527F) executes in the User's Local Temp directory. Once the file is executed it deletes itself on exit.
